always begin
  forever #5 clk = ~clk;
end
or just:


always #5 clk = ~clk;   always @(posedge clk) begin
  // JK flip-flop logic
end
Use forever in testbench only for generating signals or looping test cases.
Never use forever in design logic â€” use always @(posedge clk) instead.
Uses \t (tab) for nice spacing between values.
